ABOUT THE DISTRICT
Springfield Public Schools is located in Springfield, Oregon, in the heart of the Willamette Valley, and serves 185 square miles of the city of Springfield and East/Central Lane County. We are directly to the East of Eugene, where the University of Oregon is located. We currently have approximately 10,000 students, over 1,400 staff members and over 600 teachers in our kindergarten through grade 12 school district. Springfield Public Schools believes student success is our most important outcome. The success of our students depends on the collective community coming together to support “Every Student, Every Day” throughout their K-12 education.

Springfield Public Schools commits to honoring the dignity of every student by creating just, equitable, and fully welcoming environments for learning.

ABOUT THE POSITION
Springfield Public Schools seeks outstanding candidates for the position of Head Boy's Varsity Soccer Coach at Springfield High School for the 2026-2027 School Year. This person is responsible for promoting the philosophy and objectives of the OSAA, adherence to all department policies and procedures, as well as the rules and regulations of Springfield High School, Springfield School District and the OSAA. Springfield High School is committed to creating a more inclusive and diverse student and staff population, so we seek candidates with demonstrated potential to contribute positively to our diverse community.
The Head Coach is expected to conduct him/herself in a loyal, honest, responsible, ethical and professional manner at all times.

Successful candidates will possess the following qualifications:

QUALIFICATIONS REQUIRED:
Coaching experience;
Soccer knowledge and playing experience;
Ability to work with high school students;
Effective communication skills;
Ability to work within school district guidelines and budget;
ASEP and First Aid Certified;
Availability for daily practices and matches;
Ability to be District Van Certified;
Ability and commitment to practice cultural competency and demonstrate respect for diversity.

QUALIFICATIONS DESIRED:
3-5 years of coaching experience at the high school level or beyond;
Experience working with high school age students;
Fundraising knowledge and/or capabilities;
Understanding of OSAA rules and regulations;
Good organizational skills;
Ability to work with individuals and large groups;
Ability to work with parents and booster clubs.

